# to create a partition on disk /dev/xvdf
fdisk /dev/xvdf
# Command (m for help): m    - help
# Command (m for help): p    - (print) show all current partitions on the disk
# Command (m for help): g    - create a new empty GPT partition table
# Command (m for help): n    -
# Partition number (1-128, default 1):            - use default
# First sector (2048-2097118, default 2048):      - use default
# Last sector, +sectors or +size{K,M,G,T,P} (2048-2097118, default 2048): +750M     - size = 750Mb
# Created partition 1        - the partition 1 is created
# Command (m for help): p    - print the partion table again to see the new partition
# Command (m for help): w    - write table to disk and exit
# Command (m for help): q    - quit